data.title: High School Track And Field Penn Relays 2024 Results
data.meta_description: Complete results from the three days of high school competition at the 2024 Penn Relays presented by Toyota, being held at Franklin Field in Philadelphia.
data.text:
One of the year's most anticipated events - the Penn Relays presented by Toyota - brought many more memorable performances to the historic Franklin Field in Philadelphia in 2024.

Among the more than 15,000 athletes who competed during the three-day event (April 25-27) were some of the top high school competitors in the nation.

The Penn Relays first was held in 1895 and has grown to feature more than 400 events over the three days of competition. The 2024 meet was the 128th edition of the Penn Relays.

Competition at the 2024 Penn Relays began with high school track events April 25 at 9 a.m. Eastern.

The final event of the year was the high school boys 4x400 Philadelphia Area Final presented by PECO on April 27.
